The thing right now though is that the A tier and S tier junglers are considerably better than B tier. An A tier jungler should beat an equally skilled B tier almost all the time assuming equal teams. They're not just marginally better, they're gods compared to lower tiers.

The tiers also aren't in any particular order, the first champ in the A tier is about as strong as the last.

Out of the champs you listed the best are Hecarim, Graves and Nid. Graves is pretty much a brain dead easy champ, so if you're not familiar with the role he's going to be the easiest of them.

adding champs that I feel you missed
A Tier: {{champion:54}} {{champion:111}} {{champion:106}} {{champion:5}} 
